li 20-Sep-21 07:01 PM
September 20th, 50 AA. LQCC Office. 6:50 AM.
A haggard awareness seeps in through the room at the notion of being here by your desk so early, let alone awake at all... Truly, your boss spoils you when it comes to scheduling a lot of the time, and this wasn‚Äôt always the case for employees at other companies, such as your client for the day. Motives behind his query aside, 7 AM was the time that he had booked to brief the investigators signed to his case, as approved by Dr. Quigley himself. In the same vein, Dr. Quigley also appointed his men onto the case at the behest of the client, who very eloquently asked for ‚Äúas many of you guys as possible.‚Äù So that was that, the rest was history, and the less acquainted were feeling like the pigment of their eyeballs would seep through into their skulls with how crusty they felt. ...The more disciplined ones- the ones who, god forbid, usually worked at this time... you guys would be doing alright, if not for the thickness of the air.
...Well. All that was left was to wait for everyone who had been assigned to come trickling in; hopefully with the client not being too fashionably late himself.
You may rp yourselves trickling in and saying good morning/waiting for the briefing <3

li 20-Sep-21 08:54 PM
Some of you are high off the adrenaline of a new lead, a new adventure.
Some of you don't want to be the one to call home, to tell the people back there that another one was lost. May as well get lost yourself, and know that you dared to try.
Some of you know that you made promises- promises that you'd never forget. With the promises of several Meteor City residents compounded, now was your chance to make good on those promises.
Maybe, secretly, some of you just wanted to go far away.
As you all walk, drive, carpool to the underground, you can't help but notice how scarce the streets look- despite the fact that it was now nearing 10 AM. The city was usually waking up at this time, but it felt... melancholy. Sullen, even. The sky smelled like rain. Perfect day to be sitting in the Underground, perhaps.
You all arrive at the Underground, analog or digital tickets in hand. They're accepted at the turn dials as one would hope, and you all find that the Underground is not divvied up into regular halls at it usually is, with stairs going up and down for various different metro lines-- there's just one line.
-PV - NOW BOARDING.

13
You find that you're being drawn to the carts, legs moving at a rhythm regardless of whether you order them to or not. And perhaps, you realize, that Ernest was not completely stupid to have gotten this far- if you're having second thoughts now too, there would be no way to break free. Absolutely. No. Way. You'll be very pleased with yourself.

17
You board the completely empty train, all of you. It's nice and toasty. How pleasant. You can sit, stand, jump wherever you want- you just can't leave.
[ . . . ]
15
-PV - NOW BOARDING - NOW BOARDING - NOW BOARDING, 0 MIN -
The carts begin to sputter alive, crawling at a slow pace as the train made for the exit. The rails are extremely quiet- very pleasant. There's funny advertisements plastered onto the walls inside of the shuttle. They are very funny. You laugh, maybe. Or maybe you're the kind of guy who types LOL! to your friend, but actually has a straight face behind the screen. Pleasantville accepts any and every one.
It's quiet in the carts. It's nice and warm, like a hug from your favorite person. Just makes you want to close your eyes- you feel like you're basking under the sun. You'll be so happy here, so safe- you can feel like this every day. The cart's quiet. Everyone is quiet, because they're experiencing this beautiful shared moment with you. Your new life is about to begin. Don't open your eyes!- (But if you do, you'll find that it's completely dark. Kind of like how it was in Kindergarten during naptime. Or maybe you didn't have the chance to go to Kindergarten growing up. That's too sad. In Pleasantville, you'll just know you've had it all.)

li 20-Sep-21 09:22 PM
Pleasantville and You!
pleasantville BOT 20-Sep-21 10:01 PM
A dazzling array of shops and skyscrapers stretch on before you into the horizon; it's clear that you've arrived at the city's beating heart. From high-end shopping centers to the city's bustling financial district, there's something for everyone, whether you're looking for work or leisure. Luxury apartments dot the landscape here too, sunlight gleaming off of sleek glass panes and spacious balconies; two branches of a huge river cleave through the city center, spanned by rustic bridges and filled with sightseeing ferries and hobbyist kayaks. For the out-of-towners, hotels of every shape and size provide lavish accommodations for tourists of any budget. The city's many train stations ferry passengers throughout Pleasantville, bus routes and subway tunnels like the veins and arteries of a vast and varied circulatory system. The streets are crowded, but not packed, alive with a steady pulse of activity.

In vertebrates and other hemoglobin-using creatures, arterial blood and capillary blood are bright red, as oxygen imparts a strong red color to the heme group. This was rather anticlimactic, you feel- but it was chock-full of that characteristic irony that made missions as spurious as they were. They were their own little contained stories, and you were the one in control of the flow- but everything was already predetermined, and your only job was to see it through to its satisfying (or gruesome) end.
